  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;The proposed rear extension by reason of its size, form and location would be an obtrusive and poorly designed extension which connects the single storey studio building to the rear of the main building, thereby resulting in a cramped appearance and an overdevelopment of the site, harmful to the appearance of the site and the street scene. The proposal is  therefore contrary to policy &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; font-family: Arial; font-size: 11pt; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character), &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;of the Hackney LP33 Local Plan, and policies D3 (Optimising site capacity through the design-led approach) and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; font-family: Arial; font-size: 11pt; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;D4 (Delivering good design)&amp;nbsp;of the London Plan 2021.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; font-family: Arial; font-size: 11pt; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed ground floor extension results in the loss of rear amenity space and the\r\nremaining garden is considered to be inadequate in terms of its size, layout and usability.&amp;nbsp; As\r\nsuch the proposal is contrary to policy LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character), policies D3 (Optimising site capacity through the design-led approach) and D4 (Delivering good design) of the London Plan and LBH&#x27;s\r\nSPD Residential Extensions and Alterations 2009.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
